OL,7,FThe Online Safety Act offence, which
OL,8,Fcarries a maximum sentence of five
OL,9,Fyears, stated that Khan was involved
OL,10,Fin sending a video uploaded to social
OL,11,Fmedia platforms on a day between
OL,12,FAugust 4 and August 6.
OL,14,FNo details of the video were given to
OL,15,Fthe court, but a previous hearing was
OL,16,Ftold Khan was seen brandishing what
OL,17,Fappeared to be an AK-47.
OL,19,FA previous hearing was also told that
OL,20,Fthe video was viewed more than 1.4
OL,21,Fmillion times on social media.
